Hi ES,

FYI, TestNG supports inheritance of annotations.

It also supports =
&quot;class-scoped&quot; annotations, which means that an annotation
declared on the =
class will automatically apply to all public methods of that
class.  The co=
mbination of inheritance and class-scoped annotations allows
for some very =
powerful approaches that let you hide all the annotations in a
base class a=
nd let developers just extend that base class and transparently
benefit fro=
m all the set up and annotations found in super classes...

